Security Analyst· Singapore, Singapore
Security Analyst
Singapore, Singapore
Full Time Employment
Recruiter Comment: We are on the lookout for an Information Security Assurance Analyst to be responsible for formulation and execution of information security assurance process in the company.
#CISSP #CISA #ITSecurity
Share:Job DescriptionThe Information Security Assurance Analyst will be responsible for formulation and execution of information security assurance process in the company.  The Analyst is also responsible for performing security events analysis as members of the company Security Operation Center.He/she is expected to perform system security and identity/access reviews working with various departments including application portfolios and infrastructure teams.  The person will also conduct security assurance review with vendors and service providers.ResponsibilitiesPerform information security assurance function and reporting on company security posture.Conduct both internal and external review of IT systems security for compliance with policies and standards.Work with service providers, application and operational support teams to drive continuous improvement in information security.Ensure security events logging and co-relation are configured and perform review/remediation of any security events.Developing and executing application and system vulnerability test plans to check infrastructure and systems security posture, reporting on findings and making recommendations for improvement.Shift duty is not required but off-duty on-call standby is expected. RequirementsA Bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university in computer engineering, computer science, or related field is required. Security certifications such as CISSP, CISM, CISA,  Pen-test, Forensics.  5-7 years in the IT profession, including 3 years in information security operations or IT compliance/assurance role. Strong knowledge on Technical/Application Systems security and Security events co-relation (Log Mgt and SIEM)Experience in one or more of the following domains preferred.Cyber SecurityApplication and System Vulnerability Assessment and Penetration TestIdentity and Access ManagementNetwork SecuritySecurity Events AnalysisSystems configuration compliance and patch managementAbility to work with minimal supervision and general direction.Experience working in a team-oriented, collaborative environment over long periods of timePlease send your resume in WORD format to yvonne.tan@lysten.com.sg or contact Yvonne Tan on +65 6332 0138 for a confidential discussion. Please note that only short-listed candidates will be contacted.ProfileYour IT Trained Recruiter
